source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-1925

Adjusting the base cyclopropane value of -127 with this increase suggests a melting point of -127 + 70 = -57 degrees Celsius. This prediction significantly deviates from the actual melting point and needs to be rethought, suggesting that the steric and electronic effects of the tert-butyl and nitrile groups have been underestimated; moreover, the base value for cyclopropane may not be the best reference due to the significant structural alterations.
